AUDIO: 'This is going to save a lot of people headache and may even save your butt on a couple of jobs. In my hands is a personal server with a touchscreen and you don\'t need a laptop to back up your footage. So, this is the UniFi Drive'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'UP6. I\'ve had it for probably a little over a month right now trying out on various different shoots and a lot of the stuff that you\'ve been seeing here on this channel. I\'ve been backing up my stuff. Man, this has been a product or something like this I\'ve been wanting on'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the market for quite some time now. There have been other drives out there that were designed for backing up, but you never had a display like this where you could actually play back your footage, photo and video, making sure that you got it right, and even'

[00:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Bluetooth connectivity, so you can actually use earphones with it or earbuds. Plus, it\'s got Thunderbolt 4, it\'s got HDMI, it\'s got Ethernet, so you can actually use this as your own personal server, edit off this. Honestly speaking, I don\'t know why it took this'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'long for somebody to make this. You have the Intel Core Ultra 5125H processor. You can put up to 96 gigabytes of DDR5 RAM. Now, it comes with 16 gigabytes already inside. That kind of just gets the ball rolling. Up to 48 terabytes. I'

[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'think this is NVME PCI 4.0 SSD drives inside of this. Now, I\'ve got 2 TB for this review because yes, storage is expensive. I know that. You know that.'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
